65	Tentang KDEKS	About KNEKS	about	Sejarah KDEKS	History KDEKS	kdeks	0	NULL	<br>	<br>	<p>Komite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah (KNEKS) merupakan perubahan dari KNKS untuk peningkatan pembangunan ekosistem ekonomi dan keuangan syariah serta menjadikan Indonesia sebagai Pusat Halal Dunia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pencanangan titik awal untuk memposisikan Indonesia sebagai salah satu pelaku utama dan hub ekonomi syariah dunia dilakukan seiring dengan peluncuran Masterplan Ekonomi Syariah Indonesia pada bulan Mei 2019.</p>	<br>	-	-	<br>	<br>	-	-	<br>	<br>	-	-	<br>	<br>	-	-	<br>	<br>
67	Tentang Ekonomi Syariah	About Shariah Economics	about	Sejarah	History	ekonomi_syariah	0		<p class="Heading3Body" style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Komite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah (KNEKS) adalah lembaga pemerintah Indonesia yang dibentuk untuk mempercepat pengembangan ekosistem ekonomi dan keuangan syariah secara nasional. Berlandaskan Peraturan Presiden No. 28 Tahun 2020, KNEKS berfungsi sebagai pusat koordinasi lintas kementerian dan lembaga dalam merancang kebijakan, memperkuat regulasi, serta mendorong inovasi di sektor industri halal, jasa keuangan syariah, bisnis berbasis syariah, dan keuangan sosial seperti zakat dan wakaf. Dengan kepemimpinan langsung oleh Presiden dan Wakil Presiden, KNEKS memiliki peran strategis untuk menjadikan Indonesia sebagai pusat ekonomi syariah dunia, sekaligus memastikan bahwa pertumbuhan ekonomi berbasis nilai Islam berjalan inklusif, berdaya saing global, dan memberi manfaat luas bagi masyarakat.</font></p>	<div><div id="Mbnck7WP9w9GNXjpeaNaX-content-0"><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">The National Committee for Sharia Economy and Finance (KNEKS) is an Indonesian government institution established to accelerate the development of the national sharia economy and finance ecosystem. Based on Presidential Regulation No. 28 of 2020, KNEKS functions as a central coordinator across ministries and agencies in designing policies, strengthening regulations, and encouraging innovation in the halal industry, sharia financial services, sharia-based businesses, and social finance such as zakat and waqf. With direct leadership from the President and Vice President, KNEKS holds a strategic role in positioning Indonesia as a global hub for the sharia economy, while ensuring that economic growth rooted in Islamic values is inclusive, globally competitive, and provides broad benefits for society.</font></p></div></div><div></div>	<p><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Ekonomi syariah berakar dari ajaran Islam sejak lebih dari 1.400 tahun lalu, dengan landasan utama pada Al-Quran dan Hadis yang menekankan keadilan, larangan riba, serta distribusi kekayaan yang merata. Pada masa Nabi Muhammad SAW, praktik ekonomi syariah diwujudkan melalui mekanisme perdagangan yang jujur, zakat sebagai instrumen redistribusi, dan larangan praktik eksploitatif. Periode Khilafah Islam kemudian memperluas penerapan prinsip-prinsip ini secara sistematis, termasuk pengelolaan baitul mal, pengaturan pasar, dan pengawasan harga untuk menjaga keseimbangan sosial. Namun, perkembangan ekonomi syariah mengalami stagnasi selama masa kolonial, ketika sistem kapitalis Barat mendominasi dan menggeser praktik ekonomi berbasis syariah</span><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">.</span></p><p><font face="arial" size="4" style="">Kebangkitan kembali ekonomi syariah terjadi pada abad ke-20, ditandai dengan berdirinya lembaga keuangan syariah modern, seperti Islamic Development Bank (1975) di tingkat global, dan Bank Muamalat Indonesia (1991) sebagai pionir di Indonesia. Sejak itu, ekonomi syariah berkembang pesat, mencakup sektor keuangan, industri halal, pariwisata, hingga media dan hiburan. Perkembangan ini menunjukkan bahwa ekonomi syariah bukan hanya sistem alternatif, tetapi juga bagian integral dari ekonomi global yang menekankan nilai keadilan, keberlanjutan, dan kesejahteraan universal. Dengan dukungan regulasi dan meningkatnya kesadaran masyarakat, ekonomi syariah kini dipandang sebagai paradigma ekonomi yang relevan untuk menjawab tantangan modern</font></p>	<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">I</strong><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">slamic economics traces its origins to the formative period of Islam in the 7th century, when economic activities were guided by the Quran and the Hadith. These sources established fundamental principles such as the prohibition of riba (usury), the obligation of zakat (almsgiving) as a redistributive mechanism, and the emphasis on fairness in trade and contracts. During the era of the early Caliphates, these principles were institutionalized through the establishment of the </span><em style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">baitul mal</em><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;"> (public treasury), regulation of markets, and oversight of commercial practices to ensure social justice and economic stability. This early framework provided a distinctive economic paradigm that integrated moral, social, and financial dimensions, distinguishing it from purely materialistic systems. However, the expansion of colonialism and the dominance of Western capitalist models in subsequent centuries led to a decline in the systematic application of Islamic economic principles.</span></p><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial" style="">The modern revival of Islamic economics began in the mid-20th century, driven by intellectual discourse and the establishment of formal institutions. The creation of the Islamic Development Bank in 1975 marked a significant milestone in institutionalizing Islamic finance at the global level, while the founding of Bank Muamalat Indonesia in 1991 exemplified its regional development. Since then, Islamic economics has expanded beyond finance into diverse sectors such as halal food and beverages, pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, tourism, and media. This evolution reflects not only a resurgence of religiously grounded economic practices but also their adaptation to contemporary global challenges. Today, Islamic economics is increasingly recognized as a comprehensive paradigm that emphasizes justice, sustainability, and universal welfare, positioning itself as both an ethical alternative and a complementary framework within the global economic system.</font></p><div></div>	Landasan Hukum	Legal Basis	<p><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Regulasi ekonomi syariah di Indonesia mencakup Undang-Undang No. 21 Tahun 2008 tentang Perbankan Syariah, Kompilasi Hukum Ekonomi Syariah (KHES), serta Peraturan Mahkamah Agung No. 14 Tahun 2016 tentang tata cara penyelesaian perkara ekonomi syariah. Dalil ekonomi syariah bersumber dari Al-Quran dan Hadis, terutama terkait larangan riba, kewajiban zakat, keadilan dalam muamalah, dan prinsip halal-haram dalam aktivitas ekonomi</span></p>	<h3><strong style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; color: rgb(107, 120, 133);">The regulation of Islamic economics in Indonesia encompasses Law No. 21 of 2008 on Islamic Banking, the Compilation of Islamic Economic Law (KHES), as well as Supreme Court Regulation No. 14 of 2016 concerning procedures for resolving Islamic economic disputes. The normative foundations of Islamic economics are derived from the Quran and Hadith, particularly with regard to the prohibition of </strong><em style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; color: rgb(107, 120, 133); font-weight: 400;"><strong>riba</strong></em><strong style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; color: rgb(107, 120, 133);"> (usury), the obligation of </strong><em style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; color: rgb(107, 120, 133); font-weight: 400;"><strong>zakat</strong></em><strong style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; color: rgb(107, 120, 133);"> (almsgiving), the principle of justice in </strong><em style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; color: rgb(107, 120, 133); font-weight: 400;"><strong>muamalah</strong></em><strong style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; color: rgb(107, 120, 133);"> (transactions), and the halalharam framework governing economic activities.</strong></h3>	\N	Filosofi Logo	-	.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;	Tugas	Tasks	<div><ul><li><font face="arial" size="4">Menegakkan Keadilan dalam Ekonomi Ekonomi syariah bertugas memastikan bahwa setiap transaksi dilakukan secara adil, tanpa adanya praktik riba, gharar (ketidakpastian berlebihan), maupun maysir (perjudian).</font></li><li><font face="arial" size="4">Mengatur Distribusi Kekayaan Melalui instrumen zakat, infaq, sedekah, dan wakaf, ekonomi syariah berperan dalam mendistribusikan kekayaan agar tidak menumpuk pada segelintir orang, serta membantu kelompok yang membutuhkan.</font></li><li><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Mewujudkan Kesejahteraan Sosial Ekonomi syariah bertugas menciptakan kesejahteraan yang merata, sehingga pertumbuhan ekonomi tidak hanya dinikmati oleh individu atau kelompok tertentu, tetapi oleh seluruh masyarakat.</span></li><li><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Menjaga Stabilitas dan Keberlanjutan Ekonomi Dengan mendorong investasi di sektor riil dan menghindari spekulasi, ekonomi syariah berperan menjaga stabilitas ekonomi jangka panjang yang berkelanjutan.</span></li><li><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Membangun Ekosistem Halal Ekonomi syariah bertugas memastikan bahwa seluruh produk dan jasa yang beredar sesuai dengan standar halal, mencakup sektor keuangan, makanan, farmasi, kosmetik, pariwisata, hingga media.</span></li><li><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Mengintegrasikan Nilai Moral dan Spiritual Selain aspek teknis, ekonomi syariah juga bertugas menanamkan nilai-nilai etika, tanggung jawab, dan spiritualitas dalam aktivitas ekonomi, sehingga tercipta keseimbangan antara kepentingan duniawi dan ukhrawi.</span></li></ul></div>	<p><b style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">U</b><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">pholding Justice in Economic Transactions  \r\nIslamic economics is tasked with ensuring that every transaction is conducted fairly, free from exploitative practices such as </span><em style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">riba</em><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;"> (usury), </span><em style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">gharar</em><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;"> (excessive uncertainty), and </span><em style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">maysir</em><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;"> (gambling).</span></p><p><font face="arial" size="4">Regulating Wealth Distribution  \r\nThrough instruments such as <em>zakat</em>, <em>infaq</em>, <em>sadaqah</em>, and <em>waqf</em>, Islamic economics plays a central role in redistributing wealth so that it does not accumulate among a small elite, while simultaneously supporting disadvantaged groups.</font></p><p><font face="arial" size="4">Realizing Social Welfare  \r\nIslamic economics is responsible for creating equitable welfare, ensuring that economic growth is not confined to individuals or specific groups, but is enjoyed by society as a whole.</font></p><p><font face="arial" size="4">Maintaining Economic Stability and Sustainability  \r\nBy encouraging investment in the real sector and discouraging speculative activities, Islamic economics contributes to the preservation of long-term economic stability and sustainable development.</font></p><p><font face="arial" size="4">Building a Halal Ecosystem  \r\nIslamic economics ensures that all goods and services circulating in the market comply with halal standards, encompassing sectors such as finance, food, pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, tourism, and media.</font></p><p><font face="arial" size="4">Integrating Moral and Spiritual Values  \r\nBeyond its technical dimensions, Islamic economics instills ethical, moral, and spiritual values into economic activities, thereby fostering a balance between worldly interests and transcendental objectives.</font></p>	Fungsi	Function	<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong style="font-size: 0.84rem;"><font size="4" face="arial">Ekonomi syariah berfungsi sebagai suatu sistem yang menjamin keadilan, kesejahteraan, dan keberlanjutan dengan mengatur produksi, distribusi, dan konsumsi sesuai dengan prinsip-prinsip syariah. Fungsi utamanya mencakup redistribusi kekayaan, pelarangan praktik eksploitatif, serta penciptaan ekosistem ekonomi halal.</font></strong></p><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial"> <strong>Fungsi Utama Ekonomi Syariah</strong></font></p><ul><li><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial"><strong>Menjamin Keadilan dan Kesetaraan</strong>  \r\nEkonomi syariah melarang riba (bunga), gharar (ketidakpastian berlebihan), dan maysir (perjudian), sehingga mencegah eksploitasi dan memastikan keadilan dalam transaksi.</font></p></li><li><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial"><strong>Redistribusi Kekayaan</strong>  \r\nMelalui instrumen seperti zakat, infaq, dan wakaf, ekonomi syariah melakukan redistribusi kekayaan untuk mengurangi ketimpangan dan mendukung kesejahteraan sosial.</font></p></li><li><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial"><strong>Meningkatkan Kesejahteraan Sosial</strong>  \r\nSistem ini menekankan kesejahteraan kolektif, memastikan bahwa pertumbuhan ekonomi memberikan manfaat bagi masyarakat secara luas, bukan hanya individu atau korporasi.</font></p></li><li><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial"><strong>Menjaga Stabilitas Ekonomi</strong>  \r\nDengan mencegah aktivitas spekulatif dan mendorong investasi di sektor riil, ekonomi syariah berkontribusi pada pembangunan ekonomi yang berkelanjutan dan stabil.</font></p></li><li><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial"><strong>Mendorong Praktik Bisnis yang Etis</strong>  \r\nEkonomi syariah mengintegrasikan nilai-nilai moral dan spiritual ke dalam aktivitas ekonomi, sehingga memastikan bahwa bisnis dijalankan secara bertanggung jawab dan etis.</font></p></li><li><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial"><strong>Mendukung Pengembangan Ekosistem Halal</strong>  \r\nEkonomi syariah mengatur produksi, distribusi, dan konsumsi agar sesuai dengan standar halal, mencakup sektor keuangan, makanan, farmasi, kosmetik, pariwisata, serta media.</font></p></li></ul>	<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Islamic economics functions as a system that ensures justice, welfare, and sustainability by regulating production, distribution, and consumption in accordance with Sharia principles. Its core functions include wealth redistribution, prohibition of exploitative practices, and the creation of a halal economic ecosystem.</span></p><div></div><h3 style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial" style="font-weight: normal;"> Key Functions of Islamic Economics</font></h3><ul><li><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Ensuring Justice and Equity  \r\nIslamic economics prohibits riba (usury), gharar (excessive uncertainty), and maysir (gambling), thereby preventing exploitation and ensuring fairness in transactions.</font></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Wealth Redistribution  \r\nThrough instruments such as <em>zakat</em>, <em>infaq</em>, and <em>waqf</em>, Islamic economics redistributes wealth to reduce inequality and support social welfare.</font></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Promoting Social Welfare  \r\nThe system emphasizes collective well-being, ensuring that economic growth benefits society at large, not just individuals or corporations.</font></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Maintaining Economic Stability  \r\nBy discouraging speculative activities and encouraging real-sector investments, Islamic economics contributes to sustainable and stable economic development.</font></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Encouraging Ethical Business Practices  \r\nIslamic economics integrates moral and spiritual values into economic activities, ensuring that businesses operate responsibly and ethically.</font></p></li><li class="ps-2" style="opacity: 1;"><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Supporting Halal Ecosystem Development  \r\nIt regulates production, distribution, and consumption to ensure compliance with halal standards, covering sectors such as finance, food, pharmaceuticals, cosmetics, tourism, and media.</font></p></li></ul>
1	Tentang KNEKS	About KNEKS	about	Sejarah	History	kneks	0	\N	<p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="5" face="arial">K</font><font face="arial" size="4">omite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah (KNEKS) lahir sebagai wujud komitmen pemerintah Indonesia untuk menjadikan ekonomi syariah sebagai salah satu pilar pembangunan nasional. Lembaga ini berfungsi sebagai pusat koordinasi lintas kementerian dan lembaga dalam merancang kebijakan, memperkuat regulasi, serta mendorong inovasi di sektor ekonomi berbasis syariah. Dengan struktur kepemimpinan yang langsung melibatkan Presiden dan Wakil Presiden, KNEKS memiliki posisi strategis untuk memastikan bahwa pengembangan industri halal, keuangan syariah, dan bisnis berbasis nilai Islam berjalan terpadu dan selaras dengan visi besar Indonesia sebagai pusat ekonomi syariah dunia. Kehadiran KNEKS juga menjadi simbol bahwa ekonomi syariah bukan sekadar alternatif, melainkan bagian integral dari sistem ekonomi nasional yang inklusif dan berdaya saing global.</font></p><p></p>	<p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">The National Committee for Sharia Economy and Finance (KNEKS) was established as a manifestation of the Indonesian governments commitment to making the sharia economy one of the pillars of national development. This institution functions as a central coordinator across ministries and agencies in designing policies, strengthening regulations, and encouraging innovation in the sharia-based economic sector. With a leadership structure directly involving the President and Vice President, KNEKS holds a strategic position to ensure that the development of the halal industry, sharia finance, and businesses based on Islamic values runs in an integrated manner, aligned with Indonesias grand vision to become a global hub for the sharia economy. The presence of KNEKS also symbolizes that the sharia economy is not merely an alternative, but an integral part of the national economic system that is inclusive and globally competitive.</font></p><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Throughout its journey, KNEKS has not only focused on strengthening the sharia financial sector but also on developing a broader ecosystem, ranging from sharia-based MSMEs, productive zakat and waqf, to infrastructure supporting the halal industry. These efforts are directed at creating a balance between economic growth and social sustainability, so that the benefits can be felt across all layers of society. The transformation of KNEKS into the Sharia Economy Agency (BES), which is currently being prepared, marks a new step to strengthen institutional capacity, accelerate coordination, and expand program coverage. Thus, KNEKS is not merely an administrative body, but a driving force that propels Indonesia toward a greater role on the global stage of the sharia economy.</font></p>	<p><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; text-align: justify;">Sejarah ekonomi syariah di Indonesia berawal dari praktik keuangan berbasis nilai Islam yang tumbuh sejak awal 1990-an dengan berdirinya bank syariah pertama, Bank Muamalat Indonesia, pada tahun 1991. Perkembangan ini kemudian meluas ke berbagai sektor, termasuk perbankan, pasar modal, asuransi, dan lembaga keuangan mikro syariah, yang semakin mendapat dukungan regulasi pemerintah. Untuk memperkuat ekosistem tersebut, pada 2016 dibentuk Komite Nasional Keuangan Syariah (KNKS) yang kemudian bertransformasi menjadi Komite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah (KNEKS) melalui Peraturan Presiden No. 28 Tahun 2020. KNEKS hadir sebagai lembaga koordinasi nasional yang bertugas mempercepat pengembangan industri halal, keuangan syariah, dan bisnis berbasis syariah, sekaligus menegaskan ambisi Indonesia menjadi pusat ekonomi syariah dunia.</span></p>	<div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">The history of the sharia economy in Indonesia began with the practice of Islamic-based financial activities that grew in the early 1990s, marked by the establishment of the first sharia bank, Bank Muamalat Indonesia, in 1991. This development later expanded into various sectors, including banking, capital markets, insurance, and sharia microfinance institutions, which increasingly gained government regulatory support. To strengthen this ecosystem, in 2016 the National Sharia Finance Committee (KNKS) was formed, which then transformed into the National Committee for Sharia Economy and Finance (KNEKS) through Presidential Regulation No. 28 of 2020. KNEKS was established as a national coordinating body tasked with accelerating the development of the halal industry, sharia finance, and sharia-based businesses, while affirming Indonesias ambition to become a global hub for the sharia economy.</span></div>	Landasan Hukum	Legal Basis	<div><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="4">Peraturan Presiden RI No. 28 tahun 2020 tentang Komite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah</font></div>	.<span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Peraturan Presiden RI No. 28 tahun 2020 tentang Komite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah</span>	====-	-----	<font color="#000000" face="arial" size="4">-</font>	-	Tugas	Tasks	<div style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">Komite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah (KNEKS) memiliki tugas utama sebagai penggerak dan koordinator dalam mempercepat pengembangan ekosistem ekonomi syariah di Indonesia. Lembaga ini berperan merancang kebijakan, memperkuat regulasi, serta mengintegrasikan program lintas kementerian dan lembaga agar sektor-sektor seperti industri halal, jasa keuangan syariah, bisnis berbasis syariah, serta keuangan sosial seperti zakat dan wakaf dapat tumbuh secara terpadu. Dengan kepemimpinan langsung Presiden dan Wakil Presiden, KNEKS memastikan arah pembangunan ekonomi syariah berjalan strategis, inklusif, dan berdaya saing global, sehingga Indonesia tidak hanya memperkuat fondasi ekonomi domestik, tetapi juga menegaskan posisinya sebagai calon pusat ekonomi syariah dunia.</font></div>	<div style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial" style="" size="4">The National Committee for Sharia Economy and Finance (KNEKS) has the primary duty of acting as a driver and coordinator to accelerate the development of the sharia economic ecosystem in Indonesia. This institution plays a role in designing policies, strengthening regulations, and integrating programs across ministries and agencies so that sectors such as the halal industry, sharia financial services, sharia-based businesses, and social finance like zakat and waqf can grow in a unified manner. With direct leadership from the President and Vice President, KNEKS ensures that the direction of sharia economic development is strategic, inclusive, and globally competitive, enabling Indonesia not only to strengthen its domestic economic foundation but also to affirm its position as a prospective global hub for the sharia economy.</font></div>	Fungsi	Function	<div style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: large;">Fungsi utama Komite Nasional Ekonomi dan Keuangan Syariah (KNEKS) adalah sebagai lembaga koordinasi nasional yang mengintegrasikan berbagai kebijakan dan program lintas kementerian serta lembaga untuk memperkuat ekosistem ekonomi syariah di Indonesia. KNEKS berperan memastikan pengembangan sektor industri halal, jasa keuangan syariah, bisnis berbasis nilai Islam, serta keuangan sosial seperti zakat dan wakaf berjalan terpadu, terarah, dan berkesinambungan. Dengan kepemimpinan langsung Presiden dan Wakil Presiden, KNEKS menjadi penghubung strategis antara pemerintah, pelaku usaha, dan masyarakat dalam mendorong pertumbuhan ekonomi syariah yang inklusif dan berdaya saing global, sehingga Indonesia dapat menegaskan posisinya sebagai pusat ekonomi syariah dunia.</span></div>	<div><div id="WoZseoPbRn628mEsygafq-content-0"><p style="text-align: justify;"><font size="4" face="arial">The main function of the National Committee for Sharia Economy and Finance (KNEKS) is to serve as a national coordinating body that integrates various policies and programs across ministries and institutions to strengthen the sharia economic ecosystem in Indonesia. KNEKS plays a role in ensuring that the development of the halal industry, sharia financial services, businesses based on Islamic values, and social finance such as zakat and waqf proceeds in a unified, well-directed, and sustainable manner. With direct leadership from the President and Vice President, KNEKS acts as a strategic bridge between the government, business actors, and society in driving inclusive and globally competitive sharia economic growth, thereby positioning Indonesia as a global hub for the sharia economy.</font></p></div></div><div></div>
\.


