7	Dr. Arief Wibisono, S.H., LL.M.	Plt. Kepala Sekretariat	https://cms.kneks.go.id/uploads/structure/photo-1762507939166.jpg	kneks	<p>&lt;p&gt;Lahir pada tanggal 27 oktober 1068. Memperoleh gelar Sarjana Hukum, Universitas Diponegoro pada 1992, gelar Master of Laws (LL.M) in Banking and Financial Law di School of Law, Boston University, Amerika Serikat pada 2000 kemudian gelar Doktor Ilmu Hukum diperoleh dari Fakultas Hukum Universitas Indonesia pada 2024. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Memulai karir di Kementerian Keuangan sejak 1993. Pernah menjabat sebagai Kepala Bagian Hukum Pengelolaan Utang dan Penerimaan Negara Bukan Pajak (2007-2008, Kepala Bagian Hukum Jasa dan Keuangan dan Perjanjian Biro Hukum (2008-2011), Kepala Bagian Ketatalaksanaan I Biro Organisasi dan Ketatalaksanaan (2011-2017) dan juga Chief Change Management Officer I Central Transformation Office (2017-2019).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Pada Desember 2019 resmi menjadi Tenaga Pengkaji Bidang Pengelolaan Kekayaan Negara, kemudian dilantik menjadi Kepala Biro Hukum, Sekretariat Jenderal Kementerian pada 12 Maret 2021. Pada tanggal 17 Maret 2023, dipercaya menjadi Staf Ahli Bidang Jasa Keuangan dan Pasar Modal dan juga menjadi Sekretaris Komite Stabilitas Sektor Keuangan&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Selanjutnya, mulai 1 Juli 2025, beliau juga dipercaya sebagai Plt. Staf Ahli Bidang Ekonomi Makro dan Keuangan Internasional sekaligus secara ex-officio menjabat sebagai Plt. Kepala Sekretariat Komite dan Keuangan Syariah.&lt;/p&gt;</p>	on	Act. Head of Secretariat	<p>&lt;p&gt;Born in October 27, 1998, he earned a Bachelor of Law degree from Diponegoro University in 1992, a Master of Laws (LL.M.) in Banking and Financial Law from the School of Law, Boston University, United States, in 2020, and a Doctorate in Law from the Faculty of Law, University of Indonesia, in 2014&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;He Began his career at the Ministry of Finance in 1993. Over the years, he has held several positions, including Head of Legal Affairs for Debt Management and Non-Tax State Revenue (2007-2008), Head of Legal Affairs for Financial Services and Agreements at the Legal Bureau (2008-2011), and Head of Bureaucratic Management I at the Bureau of Organization and Bureaucratic Management (2011-2017). He also served as Chief Change Management Officer I at the Central Transformation Office (2017-2019). In December 2019, he was appointed Senior Analyst for State Asset Management and was later inaugurated as Head of the Legal Bureau, Secretariat General of the Ministry of Finance, on March 12, 2021. On March 17, 2023,&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;he was entrusted with the role of Expert Staff for Financial Services and Capital Markets, as well as Secretary of the Financial Sector Stability Comittee. As of July 1, 2025, he is also entrusted to serve as Acting Expert Staff for Macroeconomics and International Finance, while concurrently holding the position of Acting Head of the Secretariat of the National Comittee for Islamic Economy and Finance (KNEKS) on an ex-officio basis.&lt;/p&gt;</p>				https://x.com	https://web.facebook.com/	https://linkedin.com	https://www.instagram.com
1	Sholahudin Al Aiyub	Direktur Eksekutif KNEKS	https://cms-dev.kneks.go.id/uploads/structure/photo-1755655857560.png	kneks	<div><span style="font-size: 13.44px;">Sholahudin Al Aiyub lahir di Pati, 15 Juli 1974. Selain sebagai Direktur Eksekutif KNEKS, beliau berkhidmah di MUI sebagai Ketua Bidang Ekonomi Syariah &amp; Halal, Katib Syuriyah PBNU, Wakil Ketua Badan Pengurus Harian DSN-MUI, Ketua Badan Pembinaan dan Pengembagan Organisasi (BPPO MUI), Ketua Dewan Pengawas Lembaga Pengkajian Pangan, Obat-obatan dan Minuman (LPPOM), Dewan Pengawas Syariah di Bank Syariah, Multifinance Syariah, Reasuransi Syariah, dan Penasehat Syariah BP Tapera.&nbsp;</span></div>	on	Executive Director KNEKS	<div><span style="font-size: 13.44px;">Sholahudin Al Aiyub was born in Pati, July 15, 1974. In addition to being the Executive Director of KNEKS, he served in MUI as the Head of Sharia &amp; Halal Economics, Secretary of Syuriyah PBNU, Deputy Chairman of the DSN-MUI Daily Management Board, Chairman of the Organizational Development and Development Agency (BPPO MUI), Chairman of the Supervisory Board of the Food, Drug and Beverage Assessment Institute (LPPOM), Sharia Supervisory Board at Sharia Banks, Sharia Multifinance, Sharia Reinsurance, and Sharia Advisor of BP Tapera.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 13.44px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 13.44px;">This positive track record has led Sholahudin Al Aiyub to receive the Best Sharia 2018 award from Investor Magazine as a special appreciation for his contribution in advancing the sharia financial industry in Indonesia.</span></div>					https://web.facebook.com/	https://linkedin.com	https://instagram.com
